{"type":"message","id":"e92a4e90","parentId":"a4f3e784","timestamp":"2026-02-17T05:05:55.098Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_FruiitrqQwXFVGMFZIxpdpVv|fc_0b39f6bc9ae76092016993f732f140819491afab951c040410","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"# Influences — YES\n\n> Source: Josh (2026-02-16)\n> Use: brand taste library seeds (names first, links later)\n\n## Philosophy / Theory\n- **Max Bense** (German philosopher)  \n  - Tags: theory, systems, aesthetics, information\n  - Steal: rigorous aesthetic frameworks; clarity + structure\n- **Carl Jung**  \n  - Tags: psychology, archetypes, symbolism\n  - Steal: archetypal framing; symbolic coherence across brand elements\n- **Susan Sontag**  \n  - Tags: criticism, culture, interpretation\n  - Steal: sharp critical lens; anti-cliché stance\n- **Theory of the Avant-Garde**  \n  - Tags: theory, art history\n  - Steal: legitimacy for experimentation; institutional critique\n\n## Design / Industrial / Graphic\n- **Tibor Kalman**  \n  - Tags: graphic, editorial, anti-corporate\n  - Steal: bold conceptual messaging; subversion + clarity\n- **Naoto Fukasawa**  \n  - Tags: industrial, product, quiet\n  - Steal: “without thought” usability; invisible design\n- **Kenya Hara**  \n  - Tags: brand, minimalism, Japanese design\n  - Steal: emptiness/space as a feature; refined restraint\n- **Dieter Rams**  \n  - Tags: industrial, principles\n  - Steal: principle-led reduction; honest materials\n- **Michael Bierut**  \n  - Tags: graphic, identity systems\n  - Steal: systematic identity thinking; straightforward typography\n- **Massimo Vignelli**  \n  - Tags: typography, grid, modernism\n  - Steal: grid discipline; typographic authority\n- **Scott Stowell**  \n  - Tags: branding, studio practice\n  - Steal: playful intelligence; clever constraints\n- **Peter Saville**  \n  - Tags: art direction, music\n  - Steal: iconic art-direction decisions; tension of minimal vs expressive\n- **Bauhaus**  \n  - Tags: modernism, typography, form\n  - Steal: functional form language; geometric clarity\n\n## Architecture\n- **Mies van der Rohe**  \n  - Tags: architecture, minimalism\n  - Steal: structure-first thinking; “less but better” spatial logic\n\n## Artists / Art Movements\n- **James Turrell**  \n  - Tags: light, perception, immersion\n  - Steal: light-as-material; immersive minimal environments\n- **Josef Albers**  \n  - Tags: color theory, perception, geometry\n  - Steal: disciplined color interaction; systematic variations\n- **Henri Matisse**  \n  - Tags: color, composition\n  - Steal: bold color simplification; confident shapes\n- **Pablo Picasso**  \n  - Tags: form, deconstruction\n  - Steal: re-assembly of forms; concept-first visuals\n- **Paul Klee**  \n  - Tags: abstraction, playful theory\n  - Steal: playful geometry; childlike sophistication\n- **Marcel Duchamp**  \n  - Tags: conceptual, ready-made\n  - Steal: framing as the art; context hacks\n\n## Culture / Fashion / Contemporary\n- **Virgil Abloh**  \n  - Tags: streetwear, branding, remix\n  - Steal: sampling/remix methodology; quotation marks / meta-branding\n\n## Fashion / Heritage Brands\n- **Ralph Lauren**  \n  - Tags: heritage, Americana, lifestyle worldbuilding\n  - Steal: cohesive lifestyle universe; timeless materials + aspirational tone\n- **A.P.C.**  \n  - Tags: French minimal, utilitarian, understated\n  - Steal: quiet confidence; simple silhouettes; restraint\n- **Auralee**  \n  - Tags: Japanese minimal, texture, premium basics\n  - Steal: texture-forward minimalism; calm palette; refined basics\n- **Yves Saint Laurent (YSL)**  \n  - Tags: luxury, sharp tailoring, iconic codes\n  - Steal: iconic brand codes; sharp black/white discipline; elegant edge\n\n## Information / Data\n- **Edward Tufte**  \n  - Tags: information design, clarity\n  - Steal: high signal-to-noise; truthful, dense presentation\n\n## Business / Brand Strategy\n- **Kellogg on Branding**  \n  - Tags: brand strategy, positioning, management\n  - Steal: disciplined brand framework; market/category clarity\n\n## Editorial / Magazines / Publishing\n- **032c (magazine)**  \n  - Tags: editorial, art direction, fashion/culture\n  - Steal: high-concept editorial packaging; contemporary critical edge\n- **i-D (magazine)**  \n  - Tags: editorial, fashion, youth culture\n  - Steal: street-level cool; portrait-forward identity\n- **The New York Times (NYT)**  \n  - Tags: editorial systems, typography, information hierarchy\n  - Steal: clarity + hierarchy at scale; authoritative restraint\n- **Purple Magazine**  \n  - Tags: editorial, fashion, art\n  - Steal: provocative minimal luxury; art/fashion collision\n- **Paper Magazine**  \n  - Tags: pop culture, editorial, internet\n  - Steal: loud pop moments; headline energy when needed\n- **Culture Mag Magazine**  \n  - Tags: editorial, culture\n  - Steal: cultural framing; curated voice\n- **Office Magazine**  \n  - Tags: editorial, fashion/culture\n  - Steal: contemporary portrait/editorial vibe; clean modern styling\n\n## Photography\n- **Gregory Crewdson**  \n  - Tags: cinematic, staged, suburbia, uncanny\n  - Steal: film-still lighting; narrative tension; large-scale tableau\n- **David Hilliard**  \n  - Tags: portrait, diptych/triptych, documentary\n  - Steal: intimate portraiture; serial storytelling\n- **Anthony Goicolea**  \n  - Tags: surreal, staged, identity\n  - Steal: uncanny youth surrealism; psychological scenes\n- **Annie Leibovitz**  \n  - Tags: portrait, celebrity, editorial\n  - Steal: iconic portrait staging; high-production editorial polish\n"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1771304755096}}
