website\",\"count\":5}"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_koiDted1DhRyh1n0A9FGWjtl|fc_0b39f6bc9ae76092016993f73a7a408194ac2978aa7dda25be","name":"web_search","arguments":{"query":"Anthony Goicolea artist official website","count":5},"partialJson":"{\"query\":\"Anthony Goicolea artist official website\",\"count\":5}"}],"api":"openai-codex-responses","provider":"openai-codex","model":"gpt-5.2","usage":{"input":1459,"output":348,"cacheRead":6912,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":8719,"cost":{"input":0.00255325,"output":0.004872,"cacheRead":0.0012096,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0.00863485}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1771304755098}}
{"type":"message","id":"c8835f28","parentId":"ceb45831","timestamp":"2026-02-17T05:06:03.367Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_XXxPia04fmPIWWtSyILfaAhl|fc_0b39f6bc9ae76092016993f73a7a0481948a45335daa05c3ee","toolName":"web_search","content":[{"type":"text","text":"{\n  \"query\": \"Max Bense aesthetics information official site Max-Bense-Forum\",\n  \"provider\": \"brave\",\n  \"count\": 5,\n  \"tookMs\": 796,\n  \"results\": [\n    {\n      \"title\": \"\\n<<<EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT>>>\\nSource: Web Search\\n---\\nMax Bense - Wikipedia\\n<<<END_EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT>>>\",\n      \"url\": \"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Max_Bense\",\n      \"description\": \"\\n<<<EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT>>>\\nSource: Web Search\\n---\\nMax Bense (7 February 1910 in Strasbourg – 29 April 1990 in Stuttgart) was a <strong>German philosopher, writer, and publicist, known for his work in philosophy of science, logic, aesthetics, and semiotics</strong>. His thoughts combine natural sciences, art, and philosophy under a collective perspective ...\\n<<<END_EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT>>>\",\n      \"published\": \"April 4, 2025\",\n      \"siteName\": \"en.wikipedia.org\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"title\": \"\\n<<<EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT>>>\\nSource: Web Search\\n---\\nMax Bense - Monoskop\\n<<<END_EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT>>>\",\n      \"url\": \"https://monoskop.org/Max_Bense\",\n      \"description\": \"\\n<<<EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT>>>\\nSource: Web Search\\n---\\nBy the 1950S and 1960s, his interests had shifted to Peirce&#x27;s pragmatic semiotics, which views logic as a function of signs and symbols. By understanding aesthetic objects as signs, Bense linked semiotics to Shannon&#x27;s purely technical information theory, where he adapts the concepts of linguistic signs to the problem of signal loss in technological communication.\\n<<<END_EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT>>>\",\n      \"siteName\": \"monoskop.org\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"title\": \"\\n<<<EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT>>>\\nSource: Web Search\\n---\\nMax Bense | Database of Digital Art\\n<<<END_EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT>>>\",\n      \"url\": \"http://dada.compart-bremen.de/item/agent/209\",\n      \"description\": \"\\n<<<EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT>>>\\nSource: Web Search\\n---\\nMax Bense was a German philosopher, scholar, and poet. His background studies were in philosophy, mathematics, geology, and physics, and later in information theory, semiotics, and cybernetics. He was particularly influential in the 1950s and 1960s in West-Germany and internationally. He became one of two founders of Information Aesthetics...\\n<<<END_EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT>>>\",\n      \"siteName\": \"dada.compart-bremen.de\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"title\": \"\\n<<<EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT>>>\\nSource: Web Search\\n---\\nElisabeth Walther: Max Bense's Informational and Semiotical Aesthetics\\n<<<END_EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT>>>\",\n      \"url\": \"https://www.stuttgarter-schule.de/bense.html\",\n      \"description\": \"\\n<<<EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT>>>\\nSource: Web Search\\n---\\nMax Bense&#x27;s Informational and Semiotical Aesthetics von Elisabeth Walther · Max Bense (1910-1990) studied mathematics, physics, geology and philosophy at the Bonn University where he gained his Ph.D. + Sc. in december 1937. Already as a student, he began to publish\\n<<<END_EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT>>>\",\n      \"siteName\": \"www.stuttgarter-schule.de\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"title\": \"\\n<<<EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT>>>\\nSource: Web Search\\n---\\nMax Bense. Head of Information Department HfG Ulm.\\n<<<END_EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT>>>\",\n      \"url\": \"https://www.hfg-ulm.info/en/department-head_max-bense.html\",\n      \"description\": \"\\n<<<EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT>>>\\nSource: Web Search\\n---\\nMax Bense and his conception of Information Aesthetics for the Information Departemnt of the Ulm school of design (HfG)\\n<<<END_EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT>>>\",\n      \"siteName\": \"www.hfg-ulm.info\"\n    }\n  ]\n}"}],"details":{"query":"Max Bense aesthetics information official site Max-Bense-Forum","provider":"brave","count":5,"tookMs":796,"results":[{"title":"\n<<<EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT>>>\nSource: Web Search\n---\nMax Bense - Wikipedia\n<<<END_EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT>>>","url":"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Max_Bense","description":"\n<<<EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT>>>\nSource: Web Search\n---\nMax Bense (7 February 1910 in Strasbourg – 29 April 1990 in Stuttgart) was a <strong>German philosopher, writer, and publicist, known for his work in philosophy of science, logic, aesthetics, and semiotics</strong>. His thoughts combine natural sciences, art, and philosophy under a collective perspective ...\n<<<END_EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT>>>","published":"April 4, 2025","siteName":"en.wikipedia.org"},{"title":"\n<<<EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT>>>\nSource: Web Search\n---\nMax Bense - Monoskop\n<<<END_EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT>>>","url":"https://monoskop.org/Max_Bense","description":"\n<<<EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT>>>\nSource: Web Search\n---\nBy the 1950S and 1960s, his interests had shifted to Peirce&#x27;s pragmatic semiotics, which views logic as a function of signs and symbols. By understanding aesthetic objects as signs, Bense linked semiotics to Shannon&#x27;s purely technical information theory, where he adapts the concepts of linguistic signs to the problem of signal loss in technological communication.\n<<<END_EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT>>>","siteName":"monoskop.org"},{"title":"\n<<<EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT>>>\nSource: Web Search\n---\nMax Bense | Database of Digital Art\n<<<END_EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT>>>","url":"http://dada.compart-bremen.de/item/agent/209","description":"\n<<<EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT>>>\nSource: Web Search\n---\nMax Bense was a German philosopher, scholar, and poet. His background studies were in philosophy, mathematics, geology, and physics, and later in information theory, semiotics, and cybernetics. He was particularly influential in the 1950s and 1960s in West-Germany and internationally. He became one of two founders of Information Aesthetics...\n<<<END_EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT>>>","siteName":"dada.compart-bremen.de"},{"title":"\n<<<EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT>>>\nSource: Web Search\n---\nElisabeth Walther: Max Bense's Informational and Semiotical Aesthetics\n<<<END_EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT>>>","url":"https://www.stuttgarter-schule.de/bense.html","description":"\n<<<EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT>>>\nSource: Web Search\n---\nMax Bense&#x27;s Informational and Semiotical Aesthetics von Elisabeth Walther · Max Bense (1910-1990) studied mathematics, physics, geology and philosophy at the Bonn University where he gained his Ph.D. + Sc. in december 1937. Already as a student, he began to publish\n<<<END_EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT>>>","siteName":"www.stuttgarter-schule.de"},{"title":"\n<<<EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT>>>\nSource: Web Search\n---\nMax Bense. Head of Information Department HfG Ulm.\n<<<END_EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT>>>","url":"https://www.hfg-ulm.info/en/department-head_max-bense.html","description":"\n<<<EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT>>>\nSource: Web Search\n---\nMax Bense and his conception of Information Aesthetics for the Information Departemnt of the Ulm school of design (HfG)\n<<<END_EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT>>>","siteName":"www.hfg-ulm.info"}]},"isError":false,"timestamp":1771304763346}}
{"type":"message","id":"e244cf5c","parentId":"c8835f28","timestamp":"2026-02-17T05:06:03.936Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_3pMiyAGxy9g88KEuFBuBlbj3|fc_0b39f6bc9ae76092016993f73a7a108194a5f637dfc6abacb6","toolName":"web_search","content":[{"type":"text","text":"{\n  \"query\": \"Peter Bürger Theory of the Avant-Garde book MIT Press\",\n  \"provider\": \"brave\",\n  \"count\": 5,\n  \"tookMs\": 568,\n  \"results\": [\n    {\n      \"title\": \"\\n<<<EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT>>>\\nSource: Web Search\\n---\\nTheory Of the Avant-Garde: Peter Burger, Michael Shaw, Jochen Schulte-Sasse: 9780816610686: Amazon.com: Books\\n<<<END_EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT>>>\",\n      \"url\": \"https://www.amazon.com/Theory-Avant-Garde-History-Literature/dp/0816610681\",\n      \"description\": \"\\n<<<EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT>>>\\nSource: Web Search\\n---\\nSimilar books · by Peter Bürger · Art History · Aesthetics · Page 1 of 1Start over · Previous page · The Theory of the Avant-Garde · Paperback · FREE delivery Wed, Feb 18 · <strong>The Originality of the Avant-Garde and Other Modernist Myths</strong> (Mit ...\\n<<<END_EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT>>>\",\n      \"siteName\": \"www.amazon.com\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"title\": \"\\n<<<EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT>>>\\nSource: Web Search\\n---\\nPeter Burger - Theory of the Avant-Garde\\n<<<END_EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT>>>\",\n      \"url\": \"https://monoskop.org/images/d/d0/Buerger_Peter_The_Theory_of_the_Avant-Garde.pdf\",\n      \"description\": \"\\n<<<EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT>>>\\nSource: Web Search\\n---\\nWelcome to Monoskop, a wiki for arts and studies · Decolonial aestheSis\\n<<<END_EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT>>>\",\n      \"siteName\": \"monoskop.org\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"title\": \"\\n<<<EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT>>>\\nSource: Web Search\\n---\\nTheories of the avant-garde (Chapter 1) - Theorizing the Avant-Garde\\n<<<END_EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT>>>\",\n      \"url\": \"https://www.cambridge.org/cor