y":"\"Culture Mag\" magazine fashion culture print","count":5},"partialJson":"{\"query\":\"\\\"Culture Mag\\\" magazine fashion culture print\",\"count\":5}"}],"api":"openai-codex-responses","provider":"openai-codex","model":"gpt-5.2","usage":{"input":1506,"output":157,"cacheRead":31104,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":32767,"cost":{"input":0.0026355,"output":0.002198,"cacheRead":0.0054432,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0.0102767}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1771305169026}}
{"type":"message","id":"0616d3ba","parentId":"01c685ad","timestamp":"2026-02-17T05:12:54.407Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_NGS0jWUmlpamHAsxFgXvZFrY|fc_0b39f6bc9ae76092016993f8d58bc881948ef280a60651e882","toolName":"web_search","content":[{"type":"text","text":"{\n  \"query\": \"\\\"Culture Mag\\\" magazine fashion culture print\",\n  \"provider\": \"brave\",\n  \"count\": 5,\n  \"tookMs\": 706,\n  \"results\": [\n    {\n      \"title\": \"\\n<<<EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT>>>\\nSource: Web Search\\n---\\nFashion & Culture - Periodicals by Title and Subject - LibGuides at Fashion Institute of Technology\\n<<<END_EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT>>>\",\n      \"url\": \"https://fitnyc.libguides.com/periodicals-by-subject/fashion-and-culture\",\n      \"description\": \"\\n<<<EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT>>>\\nSource: Web Search\\n---\\nPublished in France and covering ... culture and more. ... November/December/January 2009/2010 (n10)-Fall/Winter 2015 (n34). (with gaps) 5x per year Published in Spain, a unique fashion and arts magazine with an international scope that includes cutting edge content ... 2022 (n1)-Current. Annual Mildew is an annual print magazine about ...\\n<<<END_EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT>>>\",\n      \"siteName\": \"fitnyc.libguides.com\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"title\": \"\\n<<<EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT>>>\\nSource: Web Search\\n---\\nr/popculturechat on Reddit: Pop Culture Magazines\\n<<<END_EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT>>>\",\n      \"url\": \"https://www.reddit.com/r/popculturechat/comments/1hpms29/pop_culture_magazines/\",\n      \"description\": \"\\n<<<EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT>>>\\nSource: Web Search\\n---\\nInterview, Hunger Magazine, Who What Wear, Wonderland, W Mag, Dazed, Paper Magazine, V Magazine &amp; any Vogue regional mag. Those are the best ones I’ve found for pop culture &amp; celeb fashion spreads. ... Some of the more mainstream high-fashion mags skew a little old/rich, like Vogue and Vanity Fair. Vanity Fair has good/serious articles though. Maybe try Nylon, Interview, or ID. Head over to your local Barnes and Noble or whatever, grab a seat and thumb through the ones you think are cool. ... Sadly, Nylon no longer prints.\\n<<<END_EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT>>>\",\n      \"published\": \"December 30, 2024\",\n      \"siteName\": \"www.reddit.com\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"title\": \"\\n<<<EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT>>>\\nSource: Web Search\\n---\\nOur Culture Mag - Wikipedia\\n<<<END_EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT>>>\",\n      \"url\": \"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Our_Culture_Mag\",\n      \"description\": \"\\n<<<EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT>>>\\nSource: Web Search\\n---\\nOur Culture Mag (stylised ourculture) is a <strong>British arts and culture online magazine launched in 2016 by Modestas Mankus, based in Cambridge, England</strong>. It covers film, fashion, music, art, photography and literature. In 2016, Modestas Mankus launched Our Culture Mag, an online magazine covering ...\\n<<<END_EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT>>>\",\n      \"published\": \"April 15, 2025\",\n      \"siteName\": \"en.wikipedia.org\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"title\": \"\\n<<<EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT>>>\\nSource: Web Search\\n---\\nFLUX MAGAZINE | Art, Music, Film, Fashion & Lifestyle Magazine\\n<<<END_EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT>>>\",\n      \"url\": \"https://www.fluxmagazine.com/\",\n      \"description\": \"\\n<<<EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT>>>\\nSource: Web Search\\n---\\n<strong>Intrepid fashion, music, art, film, technology &amp; culture magazine</strong>. From fanzine to style bible to digital since 1997: stimulate. challenge. evolve.\\n<<<END_EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT>>>\",\n      \"siteName\": \"www.fluxmagazine.com\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"title\": \"\\n<<<EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT>>>\\nSource: Web Search\\n---\\nOur Culture Mag\\n<<<END_EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT>>>\",\n      \"url\": \"https://ourculturemag.com/\",\n      \"description\": \"\\n<<<EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT>>>\\nSource: Web Search\\n---\\nOur Culture - Find out all the latest news, reviews and interviews concerning film, fashion, music and art. Your source for all things arts &amp; culture.\\n<<<END_EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT>>>\",\n      \"published\": \"April 8, 2017\",\n      \"siteName\": \"ourculturemag.com\"\n    }\n  ]\n}"}],"details":{"query":"\"Culture Mag\" magazine fashion culture print","provider":"brave","count":5,"tookMs":706,"results":[{"title":"\n<<<EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT>>>\nSource: Web Search\n---\nFashion & Culture - Periodicals by Title and Subject - LibGuides at Fashion Institute of Technology\n<<<END_EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT>>>","url":"https://fitnyc.libguides.com/periodicals-by-subject/fashion-and-culture","description":"\n<<<EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT>>>\nSource: Web Search\n---\nPublished in France and covering ... culture and more. ... November/December/January 2009/2010 (n10)-Fall/Winter 2015 (n34). (with gaps) 5x per year Published in Spain, a unique fashion and arts magazine with an international scope that includes cutting edge content ... 2022 (n1)-Current. Annual Mildew is an annual print magazine about ...\n<<<END_EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT>>>","siteName":"fitnyc.libguides.com"},{"title":"\n<<<EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT>>>\nSource: Web Search\n---\nr/popculturechat on Reddit: Pop Culture Magazines\n<<<END_EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT>>>","url":"https://www.reddit.com/r/popculturechat/comments/1hpms29/pop_culture_magazines/","description":"\n<<<EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT>>>\nSource: Web Search\n---\nInterview, Hunger Magazine, Who What Wear, Wonderland, W Mag, Dazed, Paper Magazine, V Magazine &amp; any Vogue regional mag. Those are the best ones I’ve found for pop culture &amp; celeb fashion spreads. ... Some of the more mainstream high-fashion mags skew a little old/rich, like Vogue and Vanity Fair. Vanity Fair has good/serious articles though. Maybe try Nylon, Interview, or ID. Head over to your local Barnes and Noble or whatever, grab a seat and thumb through the ones you think are cool. ... Sadly, Nylon no longer prints.\n<<<END_EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT>>>","published":"December 30, 2024","siteName":"www.reddit.com"},{"title":"\n<<<EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT>>>\nSource: Web Search\n---\nOur Culture Mag - Wikipedia\n<<<END_EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT>>>","url":"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Our_Culture_Mag","description":"\n<<<EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT>>>\nSource: Web Search\n---\nOur Culture Mag (stylised ourculture) is a <strong>British arts and culture online magazine launched in 2016 by Modestas Mankus, based in Cambridge, England</strong>. It covers film, fashion, music, art, photography and literature. In 2016, Modestas Mankus launched Our Culture Mag, an online magazine covering ...\n<<<END_EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT>>>","published":"April 15, 2025","siteName":"en.wikipedia.org"},{"title":"\n<<<EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT>>>\nSource: Web Search\n---\nFLUX MAGAZINE | Art, Music, Film, Fashion & Lifestyle Magazine\n<<<END_EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT>>>","url":"https://www.fluxmagazine.com/","description":"\n<<<EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT>>>\nSource: Web Search\n---\n<strong>Intrepid fashion, music, art, film, technology &amp; culture magazine</strong>. From fanzine to style bible to digital since 1997: stimulate. challenge. evolve.\n<<<END_EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT>>>","siteName":"www.fluxmagazine.com"},{"title":"\n<<<EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT>>>\nSource: Web Search\n---\nOur Culture Mag\n<<<END_EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT>>>","url":"https://ourculturemag.com/","description":"\n<<<EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT>>>\nSource: Web Search\n---\nOur Culture - Find out all the latest news, reviews and interviews concerning film, fashion, music and art. Your source for all things arts &amp; culture.\n<<<END_EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT>>>","published":"April 8, 2017","siteName":"ourculturemag.com"}]},"isError":false,"timestamp":1771305174384}}
{"type":"message","id":"b3385a8b","parentId":"0616d3ba","timestamp":"2026-02-17T05:13:06.448Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"**Clarifying magazine reference**\n\nI’m not entirely sure, but maybe the user is referring to \"Our Culture Mag.\" I’ll check for information regarding \"Culture Mag Magazine\" and use the website ourculturemag.com as a source. I should note this ambiguity to ensure I'm covering all bases. Now it seems like I need to write dossiers for various magazines, which sounds like a fun task! Let’s get started!","thinkingSignature":"{\"id\":\"rs_0b39f6bc9ae76092016993f8d7a1c8819499321abff9a69e21\",\"type\":\"reasoning\",\"encrypted_content\":\"gAAAAABpk_jarXFtQMBJq-YOy-kbFDJZzqOR1fOW28wwqp1i98SiUUHmOcszWrutJ4tDdUNEffz4Ko_IbEcudPfj9fvq5tLF_9Co_P9t-glJAWsvZKhiHSzLTRhqYPUY1zrcWReoNb7MyyBB4B_o1bud6es_iB1S8YHmmRsZtIpt15zleSYVQlORFYQT5Ipuh5XZ-Er-fLE8FQ6R-PFAMgX5KI9sj4wYHxFovQRAhKkL6xc_umHpocMBEaAHcYHZQup9lxujLfCJ7MW6qbPxVg7TqcHPYUvRlXk8nGLZ0yOz3Xb3YJx0ToykbFNZ30-Grr95PURts-wJKhGCTdBQB_p1D_esDQJFmX25UXzqDM6XY_vo0Ajyd-eGd7oyE5fuhYkSz0lKaauQ_-gUp_zV3G-C85Q2-Ou_oKVz1Y3lvTFOPCLcFuU4ogZSuDy_nLRICIQShtx534phCzEDCjyB0xAsL4jzTL5Pz1TMv5iBYMEe1HEDJlTf8ydTjQj9a-8qEqq529sQF1VWHw8_IhKsN3g29naTd_ygdoK_GlL5bVovkNf8S7N_s-eorLxBdGJr7nWp1VHlfp6M2eE4mdo8V0bbl8P7up6kw3OrmY2fu9uD_H5F8uodkGEj1G82WxQuOioPBrwgHSrnZn293NRTKkkTuopSLfTCn5XD0-QlTRm5vyFys-C-XGEUoug3my1asBUkE_1Gdm_2r5xGyrvQMM6Bhqb0iegUQHyCEpFtDhsY10FfIvALTc6TgeahlStDVxDaErvESegtIzQycDBmOOOnvyS1QEOBHckCsFRp0HZGy3-hABti6ffOz8SPxLft8lEV9NnmQZyCpgYMqsBRLbWHpKDROPbQ15HAixmLNw6AE35JpP3g7PEFUFCz0FKcos8YR_LYfnaI_xjWAA99_ADRr5hd_bYEO5DiuL8I7u7tNdp0kHjA9C8yVJagcdLj55OAQPO4xkozl2XH5UUJHrHWKYO1lsuxMj4GRNjmsSFUP5HiOSebAD_eWm3RtWjqYBsuFnY-MDjlzQZif-TEfBPup_qCseGlVoowVlvFwpaXoOq32rGzWCA=\",\"summary\":[{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Clarifying magazine reference**\\n\\nI’m not entirely sure, but maybe the user is referring to \\\"Our Culture Mag.\\\" I’ll check for information regarding \\\"Culture Mag Magazine\\\" and use the website ourculturemag.com as a source. I should note this ambiguity to ensure I'm covering all bases. Now it seems like I need to write dossiers for various magazines, which sounds like a fun task! Let’s get started!\"}]}"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_rYVlrL7uluc0T2vG7zFyDEpl|fc_0b39f6bc9ae76092016993f8da958c8194a1032dc8d789527c","name":"write","arguments":{"path":"/Users/calbotsman/.openclaw/workspace-director/references/influences/dossiers/032c.md","content":"# 032c\n\n## 5-sentence summary\n032c is a Berlin-born culture/fashion magazine that treats editorial as a curated thesis, not a feed. Its value is art direction that feels contemporary without being trend-chasing: clean typography, high-concept imagery, and writing that’s willing to be critical. 032c makes “culture” feel like a designed object—sequenced, paced, and opinionated. It also exemplifies how to build a brand around taste: the magazine is the product and the portfolio. For Zara, 032c is the model for an editorial voice that’s sharp, international, and self-aware.\n\n## Steal this (8)\n1. Treat each issue as a *world* with a governing idea.\n2. Keep typography modern but neutral—let content carry heat.\n3. Pair long-form thinking with bold image pacing.\n4. Use art direction as a point of view, not decoration.\n5. Maintain a consistent “temperature” across disparate subjects.\n6. Make contributor curation part of the brand.\n7. Design covers as signals (not just portraits).\n8. Build brand extensions (events, product) that feel editorial, not merch.\n\n## Concrete modern applications (3)\n- **Brand magazines**: issue-based releases instead of constant content.\n- **Fashion e-comm editorial**: treat product as cultural artifact.\n- **Creative studios**: published voice as business development.\n\n## Image / visual keywords (3)\n- Berlin minimal editorial\n- high-concept fashion photography\n- clean typography, bold pacing\n\n## Primary links (5)\n- https://032c.com/ — Official site (editorial + shop + archive).\n- https://www.instagram.com/032c/ — Current visual language and cover signals.\n- https://www.magazinecafestore.com/ — Stockists/issue browsing context (reference gathering).\n- https://magculture.com/ — Independent magazine context + back issues.\n- https://www.thegentlewoman.co.uk/ — Adjacent editorial taste reference (useful triangulation).\n"},"partialJson":"{\"path\":\"/Users/calbotsman/.openclaw/workspace-director/references/influences/dossiers/032c.md\",\"content\":\"# 032c\\n\\n## 5-sentence summary\\n032c is a Berlin-born culture/fashion magazine that treats editorial as a curated thesis, not a feed. Its value is art direction that feels contemporary without being trend-chasing: clean typography, high-concept imagery, and writing that’s willing to be critical. 032c makes “culture” feel like a designed object—sequenced, paced, and opinionated. It also exemplifies how to build a brand around taste: the magazine is the product and the portfolio. For Zara, 032c is the model for an editorial voice that’s sharp, international, and self-aware.\\n\\n## Steal this (8)\\n1. Treat each issue as a *world* with a governing idea.\\n2. Keep typography modern but neutral—let content carry heat.\\n3. Pair long-form thinking with bold image pacing.\\n4. Use art direction as a point of view, not decoration.\\n5. Maintain a consistent “temperature” across disparate subjects.\\n6. Make contributor curation part of the brand.\\n7. Design covers as signals (not just portraits).\\n8. Build brand extensions (events, product) that feel editorial, not merch.\\n\\n## Concrete modern applications (3)\\n- **Brand magazines**: issue-based releases instead of constant content.\\n- **Fashion e-comm editorial**: treat product as cultural artifact.\\n- **Creative studios**: published voice as business development.\\n\\n## Image / visual keywords (3)\\n- Berlin minimal editorial\\n- high-concept fashion photography\\n- clean typography, bold pacing\\n\\n## Primary links (5)\\n- https://032c.com/ — Official site (editorial + shop + archive).\\n- https://www.instagram.com/032c/ — Current visual language and cover signals.\\n- https://www.magazinecafestore.com/ — Stockists/issue browsing context (reference gathering).\\n- https://magculture.com/ — Independent magazine context + back issues.\\n- https://www.thegentlewoman.co.uk/ — Adjacent editorial taste reference (useful triangulation).\\n\"}"}],"api":"openai-codex-responses","provider":"openai-codex","model":"gpt-5.2","usage":{"input":1164,"output":528,"cacheRead":32640,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":34332,"cost":{"input":0.002037,"output":0.007392,"cacheRead":0.005712,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0.015141}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1771305174407}}
