that enforce coherence.  \\n  Refs: https://www.vignelli.com/\\n- **Scott Stowell / Open** — playful intelligence. Steal: one unexpected twist per piece; constraints as idea engines.  \\n  Refs: https://notclosed.com/\\n- **Peter Saville** — cool framing + controlled ambiguity. Steal: omission as a system; references framed with perfect proportion.  \\n  Refs: https://www.petersaville.com/\\n- **Bauhaus** — modern design as pedagogy + production. Steal: internal “school” (principles/exercises) + cross-discipline coherence.  \\n  Refs: https://www.bauhaus-dessau.de/en/\\n\\n## Architecture\\n- **Mies van der Rohe** — structure-first calm authority. Steal: minimal surfaces demand perfect detail; choreograph space like UX.  \\n  Refs: https://www.miesvanderrohe-stiftung.com/\\n\\n## Fine Art / Conceptual Art\\n- **James Turrell** — light as material. Steal: design attention and time; atmosphere as brand asset.\\n  Refs: https://jamesturrell.com/\\n- **Josef Albers** — color as relationship. Steal: fixed form + controlled variation; palette grammar, not swatch lists.  \\n  Refs: https://www.albersfoundation.org/\\n- **Henri Matisse** — simplification with joy. Steal: bold flat color + confident contour; cut-out thinking (big pieces).  \\n  Refs: https://www.tate.org.uk/art/artists/henri-matisse-1563\\n- **Pablo Picasso** — concept survives formal reinvention. Steal: aggressive iteration; reassemble form to reveal essentials.  \\n  Refs: https://www.museepicassoparis.fr/en\\n- **Paul Klee** — playful systems. Steal: visual alphabet + grid-under-play; authored symbols that recombine.  \\n  Refs: https://www.zpk.org/en/collection\\n- **Marcel Duchamp** — framing as authorship. Steal: naming/context/provenance can transform value more than new visuals.  \\n  Refs: https://www.philamuseum.org/collections/artist/duchamp-marcel\\n\\n## Culture / Fashion\\n- **Virgil Abloh** — remix + distribution. Steal: citations as content; modular motifs across categories; build a platform that hosts culture.  \\n  Refs: https://www.virgilabloh.com/\\n\\n## Fashion / Heritage Brands\\n- **Ralph Lauren** — lifestyle worldbuilding. Steal: cohesive universe + repeatable codes; sell roles/rituals, not items.  \\n  Refs: https://www.ralphlauren.com/\\n- **A.P.C.** — understatement as identity. Steal: cut/material as signature; quiet typography; repeat purchase rhythm.  \\n  Refs: https://www.apc.fr/\\n- **Auralee** — texture-forward minimal luxury. Steal: fabric proof + atmospheric color; minimal silhouettes to showcase drape.  \\n  Refs: https://auralee.jp/\\n- **Yves Saint Laurent (YSL)** — iconic codes + black discipline. Steal: few codes, repeated; sharp typography; elegant aggression.  \\n  Refs: https://museeyslparis.com/en\\n\\n## Information Design\\n- **Edward Tufte** — high signal-to-noise. Steal: dense truth; small multiples; annotate claims with context.  \\n  Refs: https://www.edwardtufte.com/tufte/\\n\\n## Business / Brand Strategy\\n- **Kellogg on Branding (Tybout / Calkins)** — the scaffolding. Steal: positioning + architecture + governance so taste can scale without dilution.  \\n  Refs: https://www.wiley.com/en-us/Kellogg+on+Branding+in+a+Hyper+Connected+World-p-9781119533184\\n\\n## Editorial / Magazines / Publishing\\n- **032c** — issue-as-thesis. Steal: high-concept curation + clean modern typography; editorial as brand platform.  \\n  Refs: https://032c.com/\\n- **i-D** — portrait + scene access. Steal: casting as identity; consistent framing gesture; intimacy over polish.  \\n  Refs: https://i-d.co/\\n- **The New York Times** — hierarchy at scale. Steal: template rigor + trust mechanics; calm authority under deadline.  \\n  Refs: https://www.nytimes.com/\\n- **Purple Magazine** — minimal provocation. Steal: negative space as status; selection as the brand; deadpan cool.  \\n  Refs: https://purple.fr/\\n- **Paper Magazine** — engineered pop moments. Steal: cover-as-event; meme legibility; controlled chaos.  \\n  Refs: https://www.papermag.com/\\n- **Culture Mag Magazine** (likely **Our Culture Mag**) — always-on cultural radar. Steal: cadence + voice + curation; generous linking/source graph.  \\n  Refs: https://ourculturemag.com/\\n- **Office Magazine** — contemporary portrait/editorial network. Steal: social-native pacing with clean restraint; series-based publishing.  \\n  Refs: https://officemagazine.net/\\n\\n## Photography\\n- **Gregory Crewdson** — cinematic stills with narrative tension. Steal: motivated light + production design; unanswered questions as hook.  \\n  Refs: https://www.gagosian.com/artists/gregory-crewdson/\\n- **David Hilliard** — intimate triptych storytelling. Steal: sequence creates depth; autobiographical truth with designed composition.  \\n  Refs: https://www.davidhilliard.com/\\n- **Anthony Goicolea** — psychological surreal staging. Steal: beautiful-but-wrong scenes; identity/doubling motifs with clean craft.  \\n  Refs: https://www.anthonygoicoleastudio.com/\\n- **Annie Leibovitz** — iconic portrait orchestration. Steal: subject direction + lighting + set as one concept; portraits built to last.  \\n  Refs: https://www.vogue.com/contributor/annie-leibovitz\\n\"}"}],"api":"openai-codex-responses","provider":"openai-codex","model":"gpt-5.2","usage":{"input":1474,"output":2059,"cacheRead":39296,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":42829,"cost":{"input":0.0025794999999999998,"output":0.028826,"cacheRead":0.0068768,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0.038282300000000005}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1771305341445}}
