:\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Planning integration of visual section**\\n\\nI'm thinking about adding a section with a bullet list of works and links, but I realize we don't need to use the image tool since the task doesn't require analyzing existing images. I’ll just integrate the new section instead. I'm considering writing edits individually, though that could be heavy. I’ll write a script to append this section to each file before the links, making sure to map slugs to bullet points accurately. Let's use Python for this!\"}]}"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_EgJuiYXOXwCsqYgmgobbu6BG|fc_0b39f6bc9ae76092016993f9c5d4248194b76f5d79c3c8f35c","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"python - <<'PY'\nimport os, re, textwrap\nbase='/Users/calbotsman/.openclaw/workspace-director/references/influences/dossiers'\n# 3-5 reference bullets each (title — link — note). Keep image-heavy/official/museum where possible.\nSIG={\n'032c':[\n\"032c issue covers archive — https://032c.com/ — Covers + features are the visual baseline.\",\n\"032c Instagram grid — https://www.instagram.com/032c/ — Current pacing, typography, casting.\",\n\"Selected long-form features — https://032c.com/magazine — Issue-level sequencing and image-to-text ratios.\"\n],\n'annie-leibovitz':[\n\"John Lennon & Yoko Ono (Rolling Stone cover, 1980) — https://www.rollingstone.com/music/music-news/john-lennon-yoko-ono-annie-leibovitz-photos-120869/ — Mythic intimacy; staged but human.\",\n\"Leibovitz at the National Portrait Gallery — https://www.npg.org.uk/collections/search/person/mp66429/annie-leibovitz — Institutional portrait selection.\",\n\"Vogue contributor archive — https://www.vogue.com/contributor/annie-leibovitz — Editorial portrait as cultural event.\"\n],\n'anthony-goicolea':[\n\"Photography series selections — https://www.anthonygoicoleastudio.com/photography — Clean craft + psychological staging.\",\n\"Artsy works index — https://www.artsy.net/artist/anthony-goicolea — Quick scan across motifs/series.\",\n\"Wikipedia image examples — https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Anthony_Goicolea — Fast visual orientation (secondary).\"\n],\n'apc':[\n\"Denim program pages (lookbook/product) — https://www.apc.fr/collections/men/jeans — Fit + restraint as identity.\",\n\"Seasonal lookbooks on Instagram — https://www.instagram.com/apc_paris/ — Consistent palette + casting.\",\n\"A.P.C. ateliers/collabs — https://www.apc-us.com/pages/collaborations — Extension without costume-change.\"\n],\n'auralee':[\n\"Runway/collection imagery — https://www.instagram.com/auralee_tokyo/ — Palette nuance and drape.\",\n\"Official collections — https://auralee.jp/ — Fabric-first basics.\",\n\"SSENSE designer page imagery — https://www.ssense.com/en-us/men/designers/auralee — Clean e-comm photography that shows texture.\"\n],\n'bauhaus':[\n\"Bauhaus Dessau building — https://www.bauhaus-dessau.de/en/architecture/bauhaus-building.html — System-as-space; glass grid icon.\",\n\"Bauhaus typography/graphic objects (V&A) — https://www.vam.ac.uk/collections/bauhaus — Canon of forms and pedagogy.\",\n\"Bauhaus-Archiv collections — https://www.bauhaus.de/en/collection/ — Posters, objects, teaching materials.\"\n],\n'carl-jung':[\n\"Mandala drawings (concept reference) — https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Mandala — Visual shorthand for wholeness/integration.\",\n\"Red Book (Liber Novus) plates — https://press.princeton.edu/books/hardcover/9780393065671/the-red-book — Image-as-psychic system.\",\n\"Archetypes overview (institutional context) — https://www.junginstitute.ch/en/ — Anchor for terminology and lineage.\"\n],\n'culture-mag-magazine':[\n\"Our Culture Mag homepage/feed — https://ourculturemag.com/ — Cadence + readable editorial presentation.\",\n\"Interview Magazine — https://www.interviewmagazine.com/ — Image-forward Q&A culture format.\",\n\"The FADER — https://www.thefader.com/ — Scene-level music culture visuals.\"\n],\n'david-hilliard':[\n\"Triptych works on official site — https://www.davidhilliard.com/ — Multi-panel narrative format.\",\n\"Yancey Richardson gallery selection — https://www.yanceyrichardson.com/artists/david-hilliard — Curated works with context.\",\n\"LACP profile images — https://lacphoto.org/people/david-hilliard/ — Quick visual orientation + bio.\"\n],\n'dieter-rams':[\n\"Rams 10 principles (Vitsoe) — https://www.vitsoe.com/us/about/dieter-rams — The doctrine + examples.\",\n\"Braun SK 4 “Snow White’s Coffin” (MoMA) — https://www.moma.org/collection/works/4073 — Product restraint + clarity.\",\n\"Braun T3 pocket radio (MoMA) — https://www.moma.org/collection/works/4131 — Iconic geometry and interface.\"\n],\n'edward-tufte':[\n\"Napoleon’s March (Minard) analysis — https://www.edwardtufte.com/tufte/minard — Canon example of dense truth.\",\n\"Tufte gallery examples — https://www.edwardtufte.com/tufte/gallery — High-signal reference set.\",\n\"VDQI book page — https://www.edwardtufte.com/tufte/books_vdqi — Foundational visual standard.\"\n],\n'gregory-crewdson':[\n\"Gagosian works view — https://www.gagosian.com/artists/gregory-crewdson/ — Cinematic tableaux selection.\",\n\"Brief Encounters (process doc) — https://www.gregorycrewdsonmovie.com/ — Behind-the-scenes production proof.\",\n\"Cathedral of the Pines (series) — https://www.artsy.net/artist/gregory-crewdson/works — Series-level scan.\"\n],\n'henri-matisse':[\n\"The Snail (MoMA) — https://www.moma.org/collection/works/79165 — Cut-out logic + color structure.\",\n\"Icarus (Tate) — https://www.tate.org.uk/art/artworks/matisse-icarus-p11393 — Flat color + mythic simplicity.\",\n\"The Red Studio (MoMA) — https://www.moma.org/collection/works/78311 — Color as spatial architecture.\"\n],\n'i-d':[\n\"i-D homepage features — https://i-d.co/ — Portrait + scene access.\",\n\"i-D Instagram — https://www.instagram.com/i_d/ — The gesture, cropping, pacing.\",\n\"Iconic covers (image search via stockists) — https://magculture.com/ — Cover browsing and back issue visuals.\"\n],\n'james-turrell':[\n\"Skyspace projects — https://jamesturrell.com/work/type/skyspace/ — Aperture + perception as architecture.\",\n\"Roden Crater — https://www.rodencrater.com/ — Long-form light experience.\",\n\"Guggenheim artist page — https://www.guggenheim.org/artwork/artist/james-turrell — Institutional image set + descriptions.\"\n],\n'josef-albers':[\n\"Homage to the Square works (MoMA search) — https://www.moma.org/artists/97 — Series-level anchor.\",\n\"Albers Foundation images — https://www.albersfoundation.org/collection/ — Primary institutional image archive.\",\n\"Interaction of Color (Yale) — https://yalebooks.yale.edu/book/9780300179354/interaction-of-color/ — Exercises and plates.\"\n],\n'kellogg-on-branding':[\n\"Brand architecture diagrams (typical) — https://www.wiley.com/en-us/Kellogg+on+Branding+in+a+Hyper+Connected+World-p-9781119533184 — Framework visuals as operating tools.\",\n\"Kellogg brand institute/marketing context — https://www.kellogg.northwestern.edu/ — Institutional anchor.\",\n\"Tim Calkins (brand frameworks) — https://www.kellogg.northwestern.edu/faculty/directory/calkins_tim.aspx — Authority + teaching lineage.\"\n],\n'kenya-hara':[\n\"MUJI art direction (site) — https://www.muji.com/ — Living system of emptiness/material truth.\",\n\"Designing Design (publisher) — https://www.lars-muller-publishers.com/designing-design — Visual thesis and examples.\",\n\"Exhibition documentation (Design Museum) — https://www.designmuseum.org/designers/kenya-hara — Image-rich profile.\"\n],\n'marcel-duchamp':[\n\"Fountain (MoMA) — https://www.moma.org/collection/works/81721 — Readymade as framing.\",\n\"Bicycle Wheel (MoMA) — https://www.moma.org/collection/works/81697 — Selection + context.\",\n\"Philadelphia Museum of Art Duchamp holdings — https://www.philamuseum.org/collections/artist/duchamp-marcel — Institutional image archive.\"\n],\n'massimo-vignelli':[\n\"1972 NYC Subway map (MoMA) — https://www.moma.org/collection/works/78095 — System over literalism.\",\n\"The Vignelli Canon — https://standardsmanual.com/products/vignelli-canon — Primary principles + examples.\",\n\"Vignelli Center (RIT) — https://www.rit.edu/vignellicenter/ — Archive/exhibitions.\"\n],\n'max-bense':[\n\"HfG Ulm Information Dept. context — https://www.hfg-ulm.info/en/department-head_max-bense.html — Systems + aesthetics lineage.\",\n\"Stuttgarter Schule overview — https://www.stuttgarter-schule.de/bense.html — Information aesthetics framing.\",\n\"dada/computational art database — http://dada.compart-bremen.de/item/agent/209 — Digital art/systems context.\"\n],\n'michael-bierut':[\n\"Pentagram case studies (Bierut era) — https://www.pentagram.com/ — Identity systems in the wild.\",\n\"Design Observer essays — https://designobserver.com/ — Process writing as reference.\",\n\"NYC civic identity examples (index) — https://www.nyc.gov/ — Where scalable systems matter (context).\"\n],\n'mies-van-der-rohe':[\n\"Barcelona Pavilion — https://www.miesvanderrohe-stiftung.com/ — Planes, materials, calm authority.\",\n\"Farnsworth House — https://www.farnsworthhouse.org/ — Structure-first minimalism.\",\n\"Seagram Building (context) — https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Seagram_Building — Iconic grid tower reference (secondary).\"\n],\n'naoto-fukasawa':[\n\"Official portfolio — https://www.naotofukasawa.com/ — Product language baseline.\",\n\"MUJI products — https://www.muji.com/ — “Without thought” usability at scale.\",\n\"Design Museum profile — https://www.designmuseum.org/designers/naoto-fukasawa — Curated objects/images.\"\n],\n'office-magazine':[\n\"Office Magazine covers/features — https://officemagazine.net/ — Portrait/editorial baseline.\",\n\"Office Instagram — https://www.instagram.com/officemagazine/ — Cropping + pacing for distribution.\",\n\"Info page (mission/tone) — https://officemagazine.net/info — The “unorthodox network” posture.\"\n],\n'pablo-picasso':[\n\"Les Demoiselles d’Avignon (MoMA) — https://www.moma.org/collection/works/79766 — Deconstruction as new language.\",\n\"Guernica (Museo Reina Sofía) — https://www.museoreinasofia.es/en/collection/artwork/guernica — Concept carries through form.\",\n\"Musée Picasso Paris collections — https://www.museepicassoparis.fr/en/collections — Primary institutional image base.\"\n],\n'paper-magazine':[\n\"Paper homepage — https://www.papermag.com/ — Pop editorial churn.\",\n\"Paper Instagram — https://www.instagram.com/papermagazine/ — Cover-as-event distribution.\",\n\"Iconic covers index (search) — https://www.papermag.com/search?q=cover — Quick scan of “moments.”\"\n],\n'paul-klee':[\n\"Zentrum Paul Klee collection — https://www.zpk.org/en/collection — Primary image archive.\",\n\"Bauhaus notebooks context — https://www.bauhaus.de/en/collection/ — Pedagogy visuals.\",\n\"Tate Klee works — https://www.tate.org.uk/art/artists/paul-klee-1431 — Canon reference set.\"\n],\n'peter-saville':[\n\"Official portfolio — https://www.petersaville.com/ — Primary work reference.\",\n\"Factory Records archive — https://factoryrecords.org/ — Sleeve system context.\",\n\"Design Museum profile — https://www.designmuseum.org/designers/peter-saville — Curated highlights.\"\n],\n'purple-magazine':[\n\"Purple homepage — https://purple.fr/ — Minimal provocation baseline.\",\n\"Purple Instagram — https://www.instagram.com/purplefashionmagazine/ — Current art direction.\",\n\"Back issues/covers (stockists) — https://magculture.com/ — Cover and pacing references.\"\n],\n'ralph-lauren':[\n\"Official campaigns/lookbooks — https://www.ralphlauren.com/ — Worldbuilding imagery.\",\n\"Ralph Lauren Home — https://www.ralphlauren.com/home — Lifestyle universe extended into interiors.\",\n\"Polo iconography in product — https://www.ralphlauren.com/men-clothing-polo-shirts — Codes repeated at scale.\"\n],\n'scott-stowell':[\n\"Open portfolio — https://notclosed.com/ — One-twist-per-piece evidence.\",\n\"Design for People — https://www.designforpeople.com/ — Practice philosophy + examples.\",\n\"Cooper Hewitt context — https://www.cooperhewitt.org/ — Design-as-practice lineage.\"\n],\n'susan-sontag':[\n\"Against Interpretation (NYRB contributor page) — https://www.nybooks.com/contributors/susan-sontag/ — Form-first critical stance.\",\n\"On Photography (publisher anchor) — https://www.penguinrandomhouse.com/books/ — Ethics of images entry point.\",\n\"Notes on ‘Camp’ (public text index) — https://www.publicbooks.org/ — Taste codes and signals (context).\"\n],\n'the-new-york-times':[\n\"NYT front page (daily) — https://www.nytimes.com/ — Hierarchy at scale.\",\n\"NYT Brand Studio feature pages — https://www.nytimes.com/paidpost/ — Commercial storytelling packaging.\",\n\"NYT Reader Center — https://www.nytimes.com/section/reader-center — Trust mechanics as brand design.\"\n],\n'theory-of-the-avant-garde':[\n\"Book cover/edition context — https://www.upress.umn.edu/book-division/books/theory-of-the-avant-garde — Canon anchor.\",\n\"Dada documentation (MoMA) — https://www.moma.org/collection/terms/dada — Historical avant-garde visual baseline.\",\n\"Surrealism overview (Tate) — https://www.tate.org.uk/art/art-terms/s/surrealism — Historical movement reference set.\"\n],\n'tibor-kalman':[\n\"AIGA profile images — https://www.aiga.org/medalist-tibor-kalman — Canon overview.\",\n\"M&Co archive — https://www.mco.com/ — Studio work reference.\",\n\"Colors Magazine archive context — https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Colors_(magazine) — Entry point for the Benetton-era editorial look (secondary).\"\n],\n'virgil-abloh':[\n\"Off-White product language — https://off---white.com/ — Industrial graphics + quotation codes.\",\n\"Louis Vuitton Men’s archive context — https://www.louisvuitton.com/ — Luxury translation of street codes.\",\n\"Virgil Abloh official site — https://www.virgilabloh.com/ — Primary hub and references.\"\n],\n'yves-saint-laurent':[\n\"Le Smoking (museum context) — https://museeyslparis.com/en/collections — Core code: tuxedo language.\",\n\"Saint Laurent campaigns (official) — https://www.ysl.com/ — Black/white discipline and attitude.\",\n\"Met collection search — https://www.metmuseum.org/art/collection/search#!?q=Yves%20Saint%20Laurent — Object-level tailoring references.\"\n],\n}\n\n# Insert section into each dossier that doesn't already have it.\nfor fn in os.listdir(base):\n    if not fn.endswith('.md'): continue\n    slug=fn[:-3]\n    path=os.path.join(base,fn)\n    txt=open(path,'r',encoding='utf-8').read()\n    if '## Visual signature' in txt:\n        continue\n    bullets=SIG.get(slug)\n    if not bullets:\n        # fallback: point to Wikipedia + Google images query (but avoid google); use Wikimedia search.\n        q=slug.replace('-','%20')\n        bullets=[\n            f\"Wikimedia Commons media search — https://commons.wikimedia.org/w/index.php?search={q}&title=Special:MediaSearch&go=Go&type=image — Fast visual index.\",\n            f\"Wikipedia overview — https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/{slug.replace('-','_')} — Orientation + image anchors (secondary).\",\n            \"MoMA / Tate / Met search — https://www.moma.org/ / https://www.tate.org.uk/ / https://www.metmuseum.org/art/collection — Use museum databases for primary images.\"\n        ]\n    block='## Visual signature (references)\\n'+'\\n'.join([f\"- {b}\" for b in bullets])+'\\n'\n\n    # Place after Image/visual keywords section.\n    m=re.search(r\"## Image / visual keywords \\(3\\)\\n(.*?)(\\n## Primary links \\(5\\)\\n)\",txt,flags=re.S)\n    if not m:\n        # fallback: append before Primary links\n        m2=re.search(r\"\\n## Primary links \\(5\\)\\n\",txt)\n        if m2:\n            idx=m2.start()+1\n            txt=txt[:idx]+\"\\n\"+block+txt[idx:]\n        else:\n            txt=txt+\"\\n\\n\"+block\n    else:\n        txt=txt[:m.end(1)]+'\\n\\n'+block+m.group(2)+txt[m.end(0):]\n    open(path,'w',encoding='utf-8').write(txt)\n\nprint('done')\nPY"},"partialJson":"{\"command\":\"python - <<'PY'\\nimport os, re, textwrap\\nbase='/Users/calbotsman/.openclaw/workspace-director/references/influences/dossiers'\\n# 3-5 reference bullets each (title — link — note). Keep image-heavy/official/museum where possible.\\nSIG={\\n'032c':[\\n\\\"032c issue covers archive — https://032c.com/ — Covers + features are the visual baseline.\\\",\\n\\\"032c Instagram grid — https://www.instagram.com/032c/ — Current pacing, typography, casting.\\\",\\n\\\"Selected long-form features — https://032c.com/magazine — Issue-level sequencing and image-to-text ratios.\\\"\\n],\\n'annie-leibovitz':[\\n\\\"John Lennon & Yoko Ono (Rolling Stone cover, 1980) — https://www.rollingstone.com/music/music-news/john-lennon-yoko-ono-annie-leibovitz-photos-120869/ — Mythic intimacy; staged but human.\\\",\\n\\\"Leibovitz at the National Portrait Gallery — https://www.npg.org.uk/collections/search/person/mp66429/annie-leibovitz — Institutional portrait selection.\\\",\\n\\\"Vogue contributor archive — https://www.vogue.com/contributor/annie-leibovitz — Editorial portrait as cultural event.\\\"\\n],\\n'anthony-goicolea':[\\n\\\"Photography series selections — https://www.anthonygoicoleastudio.com/photography — Clean craft + psychological staging.\\\",\\n\\\"Artsy works index — https://www.artsy.net/artist/anthony-goicolea — Quick scan across motifs/series.\\\",\\n\\\"Wikipedia image examples — https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Anthony_Goicolea — Fast visual orientation (secondary).\\\"\\n],\\n'apc':[\\n\\\"Denim program pages (lookbook/product) — https://www.apc.fr/collections/men/jeans — Fit + restraint as identity.\\\",\\n\\\"Seasonal lookbooks on Instagram — https://www.instagram.com/apc_paris/ — Consistent palette + casting.\\\",\\n\\\"A.P.C. ateliers/collabs — https://www.apc-us.com/pages/collaborations — Extension without costume-change.\\\"\\n],\\n'auralee':[\\n\\\"Runway/collection imagery — https://www.instagram.com/auralee_tokyo/ — Palette nuance and drape.\\\",\\n\\\"Official collections — https://auralee.jp/ — Fabric-first basics.\\\",\\n\\\"SSENSE designer page imagery — https://www.ssense.com/en-us/men/designers/auralee — Clean e-comm photography that shows texture.\\\"\\n],\\n'bauhaus':[\\n\\\"Bauhaus Dessau building — https://www.bauhaus-dessau.de/en/architecture/bauhaus-building.html — System-as-space; glass grid icon.\\\",\\n\\\"Bauhaus typography/graphic objects (V&A) — https://www.vam.ac.uk/collections/bauhaus — Canon of forms and pedagogy.\\\",\\n\\\"Bauhaus-Archiv collections — https://www.bauhaus.de/en/collection/ — Posters, objects, teaching materials.\\\"\\n],\\n'carl-jung':[\\n\\\"Mandala drawings (concept reference) — https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Mandala — Visual shorthand for wholeness/integration.\\\",\\n\\\"Red Book (Liber Novus) plates — https://press.princeton.edu/books/hardcover/9780393065671/the-red-book — Image-as-psychic system.\\\",\\n\\\"Archetypes overview (institutional context) — https://www.junginstitute.ch/en/ — Anchor for terminology and lineage.\\\"\\n],\\n'culture-mag-magazine':[\\n\\\"Our Culture Mag homepage/feed — https://ourculturemag.com/ — Cadence + readable editorial presentation.\\\",\\n\\\"Interview Magazine — https://www.interviewmagazine.com/ — Image-forward Q&A culture format.\\\",\\n\\\"The FADER — https://www.thefader.com/ — Scene-level music culture visuals.\\\"\\n],\\n'david-hilliard':[\\n\\\"Triptych works on official site — https://www.davidhilliard.com/ — Multi-panel narrative format.\\\",\\n\\\"Yancey Richardson gallery selection — https://www.yanceyrichardson.com/artists/david-hilliard — Curated works with context.\\\",\\n\\\"LACP profile images — https://lacphoto.org/people/david-hilliard/ — Quick visual orientation + bio.\\\"\\n],\\n'dieter-rams':[\\n\\\"Rams 10 principles (Vitsoe) — https://www.vitsoe.com/us/about/dieter-rams — The doctrine + examples.\\\",\\n\\\"Braun SK 4 “Snow White’s Coffin” (MoMA) — https://www.moma.org/collection/works/4073 — Product restraint + clarity.\\\",\\n\\\"Braun T3 pocket radio (MoMA) — https://www.moma.org/collection/works/4131 — Iconic geometry and interface.\\\"\\n],\\n'edward-tufte':[\\n\\\"Napoleon’s March (Minard) analysis — https://www.edwardtufte.com/tufte/minard — Canon example of dense truth.\\\",\\n\\\"Tufte gallery examples — https://www.edwardtufte.com/tufte/gallery — High-signal reference set.\\\",\\n\\\"VDQI book page — https://www.edwardtufte.com/tufte/books_vdqi — Foundational visual standard.\\\"\\n],\\n'gregory-crewdson':[\\n\\\"Gagosian works view — https://www.gagosian.com/artists/gregory-crewdson/ — Cinematic tableaux selection.\\\",\\n\\\"Brief Encounters (process doc) — https://www.gregorycrewdsonmovie.com/ — Behind-the-scenes production proof.\\\",\\n\\\"Cathedral of the Pines (series) — https://www.artsy.net/artist/gregory-crewdson/works — Series-level scan.\\\"\\n],\\n'henri-matisse':[\\n\\\"The Snail (MoMA) — https://www.moma.org/collection/works/79165 — Cut-out logic + color structure.\\\",\\n\\\"Icarus (Tate) — https://www.tate.org.uk/art/artworks/matisse-icarus-p11393 — Flat color + mythic simplicity.\\\",\\n\\\"The Red Studio (MoMA) — https://www.moma.org/collection/works/78311 — Color as spatial architecture.\\\"\\n],\\n'i-d':[\\n\\\"i-D homepage features — https://i-d.co/ — Portrait + scene access.\\\",\\n\\\"i-D Instagram — https://www.instagram.com/i_d/ — The gesture, cropping, pacing.\\\",\\n\\\"Iconic covers (image search via stockists) — https://magculture.com/ — Cover browsing and back issue visuals.\\\"\\n],\\n'james-turrell':[\\n\\\"Skyspace projects — https://jamesturrell.com/work/type/skyspace/ — Aperture + perception as architecture.\\\",\\n\\\"Roden Crater — https://www.rodencrater.com/ — Long-form light experience.\\\",\\n\\\"Guggenheim artist page — https://www.guggenheim.org/artwork/artist/james-turrell — Institutional image set + descriptions.\\\"\\n],\\n'josef-albers':[\\n\\\"Homage to the Square works (MoMA search) — https://www.moma.org/artists/97 — Series-level anchor.\\\",\\n\\\"Albers Foundation images — https://www.albersfoundation.org/collection/ — Primary institutional image archive.\\\",\\n\\\"Interaction of Color (Yale) — https://yalebooks.yale.edu/book/9780300179354/interaction-of-color/ — Exercises and plates.\\\"\\n],\\n'kellogg-on-branding':[\\n\\\"Brand architecture diagrams (typical) — https://www.wiley.com/en-us/Kellogg+on+Branding+in+a+Hyper+Connected+World-p-9781119533184 — Framework visuals as operating tools.\\\",\\n\\\"Kellogg brand institute/marketing context — https://www.kellogg.northwestern.edu/ — Institutional anchor.\\\",\\n\\\"Tim Calkins (brand frameworks) — https://www.kellogg.northwestern.edu/faculty/directory/calkins_tim.aspx — Authority + teaching lineage.\\\"\\n],\\n'kenya-hara':[\\n\\\"MUJI art direction (site) — https://www.muji.com/ — Living system of emptiness/material truth.\\\",\\n\\\"Designing Design (publisher) — https://www.lars-muller-publishers.com/designing-design — Visual thesis and examples.\\\",\\n\\\"Exhibition documentation (Design Museum) — https://www.designmuseum.org/designers/kenya-hara — Image-rich profile.\\\"\\n],\\n'marcel-duchamp':[\\n\\\"Fountain (MoMA) — https://www.moma.org/collection/works/81721 — Readymade as framing.\\\",\\n\\\"Bicycle Wheel (MoMA) — https://www.moma.org/collection/works/81697 — Selection + context.\\\",\\n\\\"Philadelphia Museum of Art Duchamp holdings — https://www.philamuseum.org/collections/artist/duchamp-marcel — Institutional image archive.\\\"\\n],\\n'massimo-vignelli':[\\n\\\"1972 NYC Subway map (MoMA) — https://www.moma.org/collection/works/78095 — System over literalism.\\\",\\n\\\"The Vignelli Canon — https://standardsmanual.com/products/vignelli-canon — Primary principles + examples.\\\",\\n\\\"Vignelli Center (RIT) — https://www.rit.edu/vignellicenter/ — Archive/exhibitions.\\\"\\n],\\n'max-bense':[\\n\\\"HfG Ulm Information Dept. context — https://www.hfg-ulm.info/en/department-head_max-bense.html — Systems + aesthetics lineage.\\\",\\n\\\"Stuttgarter Schule overview — https://www.stuttgarter-schule.de/bense.html — Information aesthetics framing.\\\",\\n\\\"dada/computational art database — http://dada.compart-bremen.de/item/agent/209 — Digital art/systems context.\\\"\\n],\\n'michael-bierut':[\\n\\\"Pentagram case studies (Bierut era) — https://www.pentagram.com/ — Identity systems in the wild.\\\",\\n\\\"Design Observer essays — https://designobserver.com/ — Process writing as reference.\\\",\\n\\\"NYC civic identity examples (index) — https://www.nyc.gov/ — Where scalable systems matter (context).\\\"\\n],\\n'mies-van-der-rohe':[\\n\\\"Barcelona Pavilion — https://www.miesvanderrohe-stiftung.com/ — Planes, materials, calm authority.\\\",\\n\\\"Farnsworth House — https://www.farnsworthhouse.org/ — Structure-first minimalism.\\\",\\n\\\"Seagram Building (context) — https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Seagram_Building — Iconic grid tower reference (secondary).\\\"\\n],\\n'naoto-fukasawa':[\\n\\\"Official portfolio — https://www.naotofukasawa.com/ — Product language baseline.\\\",\\n\\\"MUJI products — https://www.muji.com/ — “Without thought” usability at scale.\\\",\\n\\\"Design Museum profile — https://www.designmuseum.org/designers/naoto-fukasawa — Curated objects/images.\\\"\\n],\\n'office-magazine':[\\n\\\"Office Magazine covers/features — https://officemagazine.net/ — Portrait/editorial baseline.\\\",\\n\\\"Office Instagram — https://www.instagram.com/officemagazine/ — Cropping + pacing for distribution.\\\",\\n\\\"Info page (mission/tone) — https://officemagazine.net/info — The “unorthodox network” posture.\\\"\\n],\\n'pablo-picasso':[\\n\\\"Les Demoiselles d’Avignon (MoMA) — https://www.moma.org/collection/works/79766 — Deconstruction as new language.\\\",\\n\\\"Guernica (Museo Reina Sofía) — https://www.museoreinasofia.es/en/collection/artwork/guernica — Concept carries through form.\\\",\\n\\\"Musée Picasso Paris collections — https://www.museepicassoparis.fr/en/collections — Primary institutional image base.\\\"\\n],\\n'paper-magazine':[\\n\\\"Paper homepage — https://www.papermag.com/ — Pop editorial churn.\\\",\\n\\\"Paper Instagram — https://www.instagram.com/papermagazine/ — Cover-as-event distribution.\\\",\\n\\\"Iconic covers index (search) — https://www.papermag.com/search?q=cover — Quick scan of “moments.”\\\"\\n],\\n'paul-klee':[\\n\\\"Zentrum Paul Klee collection — https://www.zpk.org/en/collection — Primary image archive.\\\",\\n\\\"Bauhaus notebooks context — https://www.bauhaus.de/en/collection/ — Pedagogy visuals.\\\",\\n\\\"Tate Klee works — https://www.tate.org.uk/art/artists/paul-klee-1431 — Canon reference set.\\\"\\n],\\n'peter-saville':[\\n\\\"Official portfolio — https://www.petersaville.com/ — Primary work reference.\\\",\\n\\\"Factory Records archive — https://factoryrecords.org/ — Sleeve system context.\\\",\\n\\\"Design Museum profile — https://www.designmuseum.org/designers/peter-saville — Curated highlights.\\\"\\n],\\n'purple-magazine':[\\n\\\"Purple homepage — https://purple.fr/ — Minimal provocation baseline.\\\",\\n\\\"Purple Instagram — https://www.instagram.com/purplefashionmagazine/ — Current art direction.\\\",\\n\\\"Back issues/covers (stockists) — https://magculture.com/ — Cover and pacing references.\\\"\\n],\\n'ralph-lauren':[\\n\\\"Official campaigns/lookbooks — https://www.ralphlauren.com/ — Worldbuilding imagery.\\\",\\n\\\"Ralph Lauren Home — https://www.ralphlauren.com/home — Lifestyle universe extended into interiors.\\\",\\n\\\"Polo iconography in product — https://www.ralphlauren.com/men-clothing-polo-shirts — Codes repeated at scale.\\\"\\n],\\n'scott-stowell':[\\n\\\"Open portfolio — https://notclosed.com/ — One-twist-per-piece evidence.\\\",\\n\\\"Design for People — https://www.designforpeople.com/ — Practice philosophy + examples.\\\",\\n\\\"Cooper Hewitt context — https://www.cooperhewitt.org/ — Design-as-practice lineage.\\\"\\n],\\n'susan-sontag':[\\n\\\"Against Interpretation (NYRB contributor page) — https://www.nybooks.com/contributors/susan-sontag/ — Form-first critical stance.\\\",\\n\\\"On Photography (publisher anchor) — https://www.penguinrandomhouse.com/books/ — Ethics of images entry point.\\\",\\n\\\"Notes on ‘Camp’ (public text index) — https://www.publicbooks.org/ — Taste codes and signals (context).\\\"\\n],\\n'the-new-york-times':[\\n\\\"NYT front page (daily) — https://www.nytimes.com/ — Hierarchy at scale.\\\",\\n\\\"NYT Brand Studio feature pages — https://www.nytimes.com/paidpost/ — Commercial storytelling packaging.\\\",\\n\\\"NYT Reader Center — https://www.nytimes.com/section/reader-center — Trust mechanics as brand design.\\\"\\n],\\n'theory-of-the-avant-garde':[\\n\\\"Book cover/edition context — https://www.upress.umn.edu/book-division/books/theory-of-the-avant-garde — Canon anchor.\\\",\\n\\\"Dada documentation (MoMA) — https://www.moma.org/collection/terms/dada — Historical avant-garde visual baseline.\\\",\\n\\\"Surrealism overview (Tate) — https://www.tate.org.uk/art/art-terms/s/surrealism — Historical movement reference set.\\\"\\n],\\n'tibor-kalman':[\\n\\\"AIGA profile images — https://www.aiga.org/medalist-tibor-kalman — Canon overview.\\\",\\n\\\"M&Co archive — https://www.mco.com/ — Studio work reference.\\\",\\n\\\"Colors Magazine archive context — https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Colors_(magazine) — Entry point for the Benetton-era editorial look (secondary).\\\"\\n],\\n'virgil-abloh':[\\n\\\"Off-White product language — https://off---white.com/ — Industrial graphics + quotation codes.\\\",\\n\\\"Louis Vuitton Men’s archive context — https://www.louisvuitton.com/ — Luxury translation of street codes.\\\",\\n\\\"Virgil Abloh official site — https://www.virgilabloh.com/ — Primary hub and references.\\\"\\n],\\n'yves-saint-laurent':[\\n\\\"Le Smoking (museum context) — https://museeyslparis.com/en/collections — Core code: tuxedo language.\\\",\\n\\\"Saint Laurent campaigns (official) — https://www.ysl.com/ — Black/white discipline and attitude.\\\",\\n\\\"Met collection search — https://www.metmuseum.org/art/collection/search#!?q=Yves%20Saint%20Laurent — Object-level tailoring references.\\\"\\n],\\n}\\n\\n# Insert section into each dossier that doesn't already have it.\\nfor fn in os.listdir(base):\\n    if not fn.endswith('.md'): continue\\n    slug=fn[:-3]\\n    path=os.path.join(base,fn)\\n    txt=open(path,'r',encoding='utf-8').read()\\n    if '## Visual signature' in txt:\\n        continue\\n    bullets=SIG.get(slug)\\n    if not bullets:\\n        # fallback: point to Wikipedia + Google images query (but avoid google); use Wikimedia search.\\n        q=slug.replace('-','%20')\\n        bullets=[\\n            f\\\"Wikimedia Commons media search — https://commons.wikimedia.org/w/index.php?search={q}&title=Special:MediaSearch&go=Go&type=image — Fast visual index.\\\",\\n            f\\\"Wikipedia overview — https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/{slug.replace('-','_')} — Orientation + image anchors (secondary).\\\",\\n            \\\"MoMA / Tate / Met search — https://www.moma.org/ / https://www.tate.org.uk/ / https://www.metmuseum.org/art/collection — Use museum databases for primary images.\\\"\\n        ]\\n    block='## Visual signature (references)\\\\n'+'\\\\n'.join([f\\\"- {b}\\\" for b in bullets])+'\\\\n'\\n\\n    # Place after Image/visual keywords section.\\n    m=re.search(r\\\"## Image / visual keywords \\\\(3\\\\)\\\\n(.*?)(\\\\n## Primary links \\\\(5\\\\)\\\\n)\\\",txt,flags=re.S)\\n    if not m:\\n        # fallback: append before Primary links\\n        m2=re.search(r\\\"\\\\n## Primary links \\\\(5\\\\)\\\\n\\\",txt)\\n        if m2:\\n            idx=m2.start()+1\\n            txt=txt[:idx]+\\\"\\\\n\\\"+block+txt[idx:]\\n        else:\\n            txt=txt+\\\"\\\\n\\\\n\\\"+block\\n    else:\\n        txt=txt[:m.end(1)]+'\\\\n\\\\n'+block+m.group(2)+txt[m.end(0):]\\n    open(path,'w',encoding='utf-8').write(txt)\\n\\nprint('done')\\nPY\"}"}],"api":"openai-codex-responses","provider":"openai-codex","model":"gpt-5.2","usage":{"input":40389,"output":4696,"cacheRead":1408,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":46493,"cost":{"input":0.07068075,"output":0.065744,"cacheRead":0.00024639999999999997,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0.13667115}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1771305398000}}
